      "content": "Ibuprofen is indeed for pain relief, but it can also reduce inflammation. If you see a small amount of yellow discharge, it's best to err on the side of caution and take an antibiotic like amoxicillin or clarithromycin, depending on your health history. Apply the antibiotic ointment, use a warm compress, and monitor the area closely. If there's no improvement within 48 hours, or if symptoms worsen, you should see a doctor immediately. It's better to be proactive in these situations.",
      "source": "target",
