      "content": "You can purchase an over-the-counter antibiotic ointment, such as Neosporin, at your local pharmacy. Apply it to the wound twice daily. For pain and inflammation, you can take ibuprofen 400mg every 4-6 hours as needed, but don't exceed the recommended daily dose. If the redness, warmth, and discharge persist for more than 48 hours or worsen, it's time to see a doctor. Self-medicating can be risky, and if it's an infection, it might require a stronger antibiotic. Remember, it's better to be safe and consult a professional if you're unsure.",
